By: Rûmi
---
When he beheld the countenance of the $adr-i Jahân. you might say the
bird, his spirit, flew out of his body.

His body fell like dry wood： his vital spirit became cold from the
crown of his head to his toes.

Whatsoever they applied of incense and rose-water, he neither stirred
nor spoke.
